events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Cleveland Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Ty Jerome scored 27 points in the first half and finished with a career-high 29 as the Cleveland Cavaliers never trailed in a 128-100 win over the New Orleans Pelicans on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ty Jerome scores career-high 29 points, Cavaliers rout injury-riddled Pelicans 128-100

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 41 points, nine rebounds and eight assists as the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Chicago Bulls 122-106 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 41 points as Bucks beat Bulls 122-106 for 4th win in 5 games

headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun had a season-high 31 points with 12 rebounds to lead the Houston Rockets to a 130-113 win over the Indiana Pacers Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sengun scores season-high 31 as Rockets cruise to 130-113 win over Pacers

headlines.description: — Jaren Jackson Jr. had 25 points, Desmond Bane added 21 points and 10 rebounds and the Memphis Grizzlies set a season-high with 19 3-pointers in a 117-111 win over the Philadelphia 76ers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jackson, Bane lead Grizzlies to 117-111 victory over Philadelphia

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Jalen Williams scored 30 points, Isaiah Hartenstein had a double-double in his season debut, and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Portland Trail Blazers 109-99 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams scores 30, Hartenstein has double-double in season debut as Thunder beat Trail Blazers

events.name: New York Knicks at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 36 points, Karl-Anthony Towns added 34 and the New York Knicks beat the Phoenix Suns 138-122 on Wednesday night for their fourth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 36, Towns adds 34 as Knicks beat Suns 138-122 for 4th straight win

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Andrew Wiggins scored 27 points, Stephen Curry added 23 points and eight assists and the Golden State Warriors beat the Atlanta Hawks 120-97 on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Andrew Wiggins scores 27 points, Stephen Curry adds 23 as Warriors beat Hawks 120-97
